PSA time:
I call my food stencils "latte stencils". This was because I started by making them for a local coffee shop. My latte stencils can be used on anything that can hold powder weight incl but not limited to steamed milk, whip cream, pudding, cookies, and icing.

Cast acrylic is food safe. Using the above cleaning methods, the local coffee shop has had my stencils for two years in an industrial setting with no change in quality. They do hang theirs to dry, there is a hole in the thumb handle to hang on a hook for drying and storage.

The stencil works best with powders, like cinnamon, powdered sugar, espresso powder, and cocoa powder. The local coffee shop makes a cinnamon sugar blend and that works perfectly too. The closer the stencil is to the top of the foam, the more defined the shape.
